00:14:12,803 --> 00:14:15,201
You know, I was trying
to keep my business alive.

248
00:14:15,201 --> 00:14:17,601
I didn't think it mattered.

249
00:14:17,601 --> 00:14:20,304
Understood. Go on.

250
00:14:20,304 --> 00:14:23,669
That day, early on, 
before I fired Andre,

251
00:14:23,669 --> 00:14:26,225
Mr. Lange offered to buy us lunch.

252
00:14:26,225 --> 00:14:31,589
So he gave me his car keys, and, uh,

253
00:14:31,589 --> 00:14:34,019
I gave them to Andre.

254
00:14:34,969 --> 00:14:36,410
- Here.
- What's this?

255
00:14:36,410 --> 00:14:38,281
That's the keys to Mike's car.

256
00:14:38,281 --> 00:14:41,517
He buys, we fly.
Better I stay here.

257
00:14:41,517 --> 00:14:42,934
But you're sure he'd want me in his car?

258
00:14:42,934 --> 00:14:44,747
Yeah, go on, hurry up.

259
00:14:44,747 --> 00:14:47,084
Make it burgers, okay?

260
00:14:49,077 --> 00:14:50,454
Heading out?

261
00:14:51,288 --> 00:14:53,649
- How about getting us some beers?
- Leave him alone, Barbie.

262
00:14:53,649 --> 00:14:55,590
Sorry, girls, can't do that.

263
00:14:55,590 --> 00:14:58,906
- So what's prison like?
- Shut up, you dork. God!

264
00:14:58,906 --> 00:15:02,971
I mean 'cause you can totally tell us
if you got shanked and stuff.

265
00:15:04,515 --> 00:15:06,756
Beep, beep, beep.
Paging Mr. Drug dealer.

266
00:15:06,756 --> 00:15:08,302
You're a total freak.

267
00:15:08,302 --> 00:15:10,154
You wanna give me that back
so I can do this food run?

268
00:15:10,154 --> 00:15:13,643
- Give it back.
- Not till he answers my question.

269
00:15:13,643 --> 00:15:15,758
So why were you in prison?

270
00:15:15,758 --> 00:15:19,220
- Sure you want to know?
- Yeah.

271
00:15:19,220 --> 00:15:22,583
Beat a man almost to death.

272
00:15:22,583 --> 00:15:25,485
- Why?
- Why what?

273
00:15:25,485 --> 00:15:28,061
Why do that?

274
00:15:28,061 --> 00:15:31,530
I was drunk, that's why.

275
00:15:32,073 --> 00:15:34,315
Guess that's why no beer run, huh?

276
00:15:34,315 --> 00:15:37,207
Give him his pager, Barbie.

277
00:15:40,434 --> 00:15:42,665
You need some help getting food?

278
00:15:44,145 --> 00:15:48,591
Andre, you still here?
We're getting hungry! Let's go!

279
00:15:56,254 --> 00:15:59,049
Exactly how long were they gone?

280
00:15:59,049 --> 00:16:01,134
Well, long enough.

281
00:16:01,134 --> 00:16:02,808
Burger place wasn't that far.

282
00:16:02,808 --> 00:16:06,165
So long enough to make 
a set of those keys.

283
00:16:06,165 --> 00:16:09,981
Which could explain why no forced entry.

284
00:16:13,037 --> 00:16:14,776
Andre never got out of the car.

285
00:16:14,776 --> 00:16:17,735
Those keys never left the ignition.

286
00:16:17,735 --> 00:16:19,818
Read this interview
you gave back in '94,

287
00:16:19,818 --> 00:16:24,039
and nowhere in here do you mention
driving off for a long lunch with Andre.

288
00:16:24,039 --> 00:16:25,463
I was 16.

289
00:16:25,463 --> 00:16:29,255
I wasn't gonna let my parents know
I tried to seduce an ex-con.

290
00:16:29,255 --> 00:16:32,335
So this Andre,
he stop anywhere else?

291
00:16:32,335 --> 00:16:34,314
Like a key place?

292
00:16:34,314 --> 00:16:35,848
Just the burger joint.

293
00:16:35,848 --> 00:16:38,561
You two were gone quite awhile.

294
00:16:39,279 --> 00:16:41,620
'Cause I gave him wrong directions.

295
00:16:41,620 --> 00:16:43,574
Wanted to get lost with him.

296
00:16:43,574 --> 00:16:46,224
But he didn't go for it.

297
00:16:46,791 --> 00:16:49,835
Got anything else to tell,
now's the time.

298
00:16:49,835 --> 00:16:53,575
It was my fault.
What happened to Kate.

299
00:16:53,575 --> 00:16:55,759
Why do you say that?

300
00:16:55,759 --> 00:17:00,307
I was always looking for a hookup,
even when there wasn't one.

301
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:05,852
Need to wrap these boxes a little better.

302
00:17:05,852 --> 00:17:08,036
Oh. Sorry.

303
00:17:14,878 --> 00:17:16,390
This box go up to your room?

304
00:17:16,390 --> 00:17:18,626
Nope. Attic.

305
00:17:18,977 --> 00:17:21,012
You sure about that?

306
00:17:24,028 --> 00:17:25,975
Nice photo.

307
00:17:27,956 --> 00:17:31,372
I learned how to use a timer that day.

308
00:17:31,574 --> 00:17:35,238
- My mom taught me how.
- Did she?

309
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:39,122
Are you better?

310
00:17:39,122 --> 00:17:41,347
Better?

311
00:17:41,347 --> 00:17:43,720
The drinking.

312
00:17:46,681 --> 00:17:50,307
Forget it, it's none of my business.
I'm acting like Barbie now.

313
00:17:50,307 --> 00:17:54,336
No, everyone's got their own point, 
see, their, their own bottom,

314
00:17:54,336 --> 00:17:57,295
when there's no place lower
you can go but there.

315
00:17:57,295 --> 00:18:01,225
And when you hit that, you die.

316
00:18:01,225 --> 00:18:05,263
Or you close your eyes and believe.

317
00:18:05,263 --> 00:18:07,900
Believe what?

318
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:12,309
There's something bigger out there
than what's eating you alive.

319
00:18:12,309 --> 00:18:14,728
Something better.

320
00:18:15,171 --> 00:18:18,249
Is there something better?

321
00:18:18,249 --> 00:18:21,635
It's up to you to find it.

322
00:18:21,635 --> 00:18:24,614
What if you don't?

323
00:18:26,152 --> 00:18:27,737
Andre.

324
00:18:27,737 --> 00:18:30,053
Need your help out here.

325
00:18:33,174 --> 00:18:35,685
You might want to hold onto that.

326
00:18:35,685 --> 00:18:37,837
Maybe I will.

327
00:18:51,615 --> 00:18:55,319
They had this connection, and I didn't 
want her to just leave it at that.

328
00:18:55,319 --> 00:18:56,368
So what'd you do about it?

329
00:18:56,368 --> 00:19:00,075
I got Andre's number off his pager.

330
00:19:00,075 --> 00:19:02,899
And did you use it?

331
00:19:02,899 --> 00:19:04,711
Not me.

332
00:19:05,441 --> 00:19:07,833
I dared her to page him.

333
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:09,531
Bugged her all day.

334
00:19:09,531 --> 00:19:13,376
- And she finally did.
- Late that night.

335
00:19:13,376 --> 00:19:16,586
And he called right back.

336
00:19:17,257 --> 00:19:22,153
So Andre called Kate
the night of the murder.

337
00:19:30,425 --> 00:19:33,058
You called Kate Lange the night she died.

338
00:19:33,058 --> 00:19:35,955
- What?
- After she paged you.

339
00:19:35,955 --> 00:19:39,007
- What are you talking about?
- We got her phone records, Andre.

340
00:19:39,007 --> 00:19:41,602
Shows all the outgoing numbers that night.

341
00:19:41,602 --> 00:19:44,480
This one look familiar?
Your pager.

342
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:47,303
I lost my pager that day 
during the move.

343
00:19:47,303 --> 00:19:49,115
- That's the truth.
- Sure you did.

344
00:19:49,115 --> 00:19:50,329
I never called that girl.

345
00:19:50,329 --> 00:19:52,387
- I got no reason to believe you.
- It's true.

346
00:19:52,387 --> 00:19:55,192
- You had her blood on your boots.
- I found her body.

347
00:19:55,192 --> 00:19:58,912
- You raped and killed her.
- I didn't!

348
00:19:58,912 --> 00:20:02,836
In the den, earlier that day,
you were alone with Kate. / What?

349
00:20:02,836 --> 00:20:06,274
That photo of her mom on the beach?

350
00:20:06,274 --> 00:20:09,759
Finding something bigger,
something better? Want me to go on?

351
00:20:09,759 --> 00:20:11,928
There's some things that ain't 
got nothing to do with this case.

352
00:20:11,928 --> 00:20:15,139
If you spent time together,
it's got everything to do with this case.

353
00:20:15,139 --> 00:20:16,894
Look, I say different.

354
00:20:16,894 --> 00:20:19,851
I don't see how talking about
old chitchat's gonna help me.

355
00:20:19,851 --> 00:20:23,114
Maybe it'll lead us to the truth,
lead you to the truth.

356
00:20:23,114 --> 00:20:27,798
I'm not gonna tell you I did it
if that's what's going on here.

357
00:20:27,798 --> 00:20:30,652
We're way past lies, Andre.

358
00:20:30,652 --> 00:20:35,389
Today's the day.
You got seven hours left.

359
00:20:35,389 --> 00:20:38,379
We're not so different, you and me.

360
00:20:38,379 --> 00:20:41,099
You and me are nothing alike.

361
00:20:41,099 --> 00:20:43,838
Two black men from the same neighborhood...

362
00:20:43,838 --> 00:20:46,422
if the ball had bounced
just a little bit different,

363
00:20:46,422 --> 00:20:50,517
you could be sitting over here
and me over there.

364
00:20:50,517 --> 00:20:54,154
I never raped and murdered a little girl.

365
00:20:54,595 --> 00:20:56,940
Neither did I.

366
00:20:58,471 --> 00:21:02,565
You want to spend your last hours 
on earth telling yourself more lies...

367
00:21:02,565 --> 00:21:04,914
be my guest.

368
00:21:04,914 --> 00:21:07,414
Where you going?
Hey, don't walk away from me!

369
00:21:07,414 --> 00:21:10,090
Do not walk away from me!

370
00:21:27,726 --> 00:21:29,271
Mr. Lange.

371
00:21:30,063 --> 00:21:32,714
I was on my way to the prison.

372
00:21:32,714 --> 00:21:35,099
Execution's set for midnight.

373
00:21:35,099 --> 00:21:38,491
- How can we help you?
- Barbie called today.

374
00:21:38,491 --> 00:21:40,180
She's torn up.

375
00:21:40,180 --> 00:21:42,285
She blames herself
for what happened to Kate.

376
00:21:42,285 --> 00:21:45,500
But it wasn't her fault.
It wasn't anyone's fault.

377
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,566
- No.
- Except him.

378
00:21:47,566 --> 00:21:50,744
And that's why I'm here. I know 
he's the one who killed my daughter.

379
00:21:50,744 --> 00:21:52,489
Okay.

380
00:21:52,489 --> 00:21:57,310
But I want to come clean about everything.

381
00:22:00,121 --> 00:22:05,180
He called Kate that night.
On the phone.

382
00:22:05,180 --> 00:22:07,728
- You knew about that?
- It was almost midnight.

383
00:22:07,728 --> 00:22:10,032
I heard the phone ring,
the two of them talking.

384
00:22:10,032 --> 00:22:12,476
Why not tell the police about it?

385
00:22:12,476 --> 00:22:14,032
More evidence against Andre.

386
00:22:14,032 --> 00:22:16,911
I didn't think I needed to.
I figured you had him dead to rights.

387
00:22:16,911 --> 00:22:20,555
And because, with no forced entry,
you were worried Kate let him in.

388
00:22:20,555 --> 00:22:22,567
If word had gotten out about that,

389
00:22:22,567 --> 00:22:25,662
people would've said
she brought it on herself.

390
00:22:25,662 --> 00:22:27,629
Right.

391
00:22:27,629 --> 00:22:30,006
I have this...

392
00:22:30,006 --> 00:22:33,966
dream some nights.

393
00:22:33,966 --> 00:22:36,078
I'm back at the old house

394
00:22:36,078 --> 00:22:39,837
and Kate and her mom are there,
we all are.

395
00:22:42,036 --> 00:22:44,680
And Kate is smiling.

396
00:22:45,227 --> 00:22:47,562
She's so happy.

397
00:22:48,356 --> 00:22:50,627
And she says to me,

398
00:22:51,837 --> 00:22:53,476
"daddy."

399
00:22:54,822 --> 00:22:56,298
"we're home."

400
00:22:58,905 --> 00:23:02,285
Sorry my dad was yelling at you today.

401
00:23:03,896 --> 00:23:05,820
I've got to go.

402
00:23:08,356 --> 00:23:12,332
- Who's calling at this hour?
- No one.

403
00:23:14,998 --> 00:23:18,152
"Andre"?
The moving man?

404
00:23:18,152 --> 00:23:20,780
What? No. God.

405
00:23:20,780 --> 00:23:23,792
Why are you talking to him, Kate?

406
00:23:23,792 --> 00:23:27,503
You wouldn't understand.
Forget it.

407
00:23:27,503 --> 00:23:30,125
Try me.

408
00:23:43,064 --> 00:23:45,776
I gave her...

409
00:23:45,776 --> 00:23:51,653
all the chances I could, your mom.

410
00:23:51,653 --> 00:23:58,960
But sometimes, if something breaks
inside a person, it can't be fixed.

411
00:23:59,554 --> 00:24:02,309
I know this isn't home, Kate,

412
00:24:02,309 --> 00:24:05,356
but maybe it will be one day.

413
00:24:07,954 --> 00:24:10,037
Hey.

414
00:24:11,058 --> 00:24:13,836
The fridge is working now.

415
00:24:13,836 --> 00:24:17,179
Got your chocolate milk, too.

416
00:24:26,476 --> 00:24:28,695
I love you, daddy.

417
00:24:30,368 --> 00:24:32,733
Love you, too.

418
00:24:41,930 --> 00:24:45,520
We never had a chance to start over.

419
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:48,951
- That night wasn't your fault.
- Yeah.

420
00:24:52,872 --> 00:24:54,692
Well, I better get going.

421
00:24:54,692 --> 00:24:57,555
- It's getting close to time.
- Yeah.

422
00:24:58,003 --> 00:25:01,012
You sure you want to be there?

423
00:25:01,724 --> 00:25:07,933
I've been lost for 12 years.

424
00:25:09,352 --> 00:25:13,067
Maybe this will bring some peace.

425
00:25:31,036 --> 00:25:33,238
Wasn't sure you'd come back.

426
00:25:33,854 --> 00:25:37,806
Been better if you'd asked
for a spiritual advisor or a priest.

427
00:25:37,806 --> 00:25:41,301
Priest can't help me now, 
you can.

428
00:25:41,301 --> 00:25:42,865
How am I going to do that?

429
00:25:42,865 --> 00:25:44,994
I'd have to believe you're innocent.
I don't.

430
00:25:44,994 --> 00:25:46,622
But you did.

431
00:25:46,622 --> 00:25:48,741
Somewhere along the way.

432
00:25:48,741 --> 00:25:51,694
So maybe you will again.

433
00:25:54,421 --> 00:25:59,460
You know nothing's changed.
Your execution is going ahead as scheduled.

434
00:26:00,442 --> 00:26:02,847
I've been informed.

435
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:08,559
Heat's about to break.

436
00:26:08,559 --> 00:26:11,288
You can feel it.

437
00:26:11,288 --> 00:26:15,288
Every since I ripped up my knee
playing summer league,

438
00:26:15,288 --> 00:26:18,946
I could always tell
when the rain's coming.

439
00:26:18,946 --> 00:26:21,097
Basketball.

440
00:26:21,097 --> 00:26:25,392
Ninth grade and it was all over.

441
00:26:25,392 --> 00:26:27,864
I wasn't going pro or nothing.

442
00:26:27,864 --> 00:26:31,636
But one college was looking at me.

443
00:26:31,636 --> 00:26:34,088
Pretty sure I could have got that.

444
00:26:34,088 --> 00:26:38,208
Tore up my knee playing linebacker.

445
00:26:38,208 --> 00:26:39,878
Yeah?

446
00:26:39,878 --> 00:26:45,198
Never got the benefit of predicting
the weather, though. Just the pain.

447
00:26:50,032 --> 00:26:52,617
I saw a man die once.

448
00:26:52,617 --> 00:26:56,225
In this place, years ago.

449
00:26:56,225 --> 00:27:01,553
He lived a life full of lies.
So many lies, he couldn't see through.

450
00:27:01,553 --> 00:27:06,142
But in here, 
in those last moments,

451
00:27:06,142 --> 00:27:11,072
you could see in his eyes
he was ready to tell.

452
00:27:12,098 --> 00:27:14,600
Tell what?

453
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:17,253
The truth.

454
00:27:19,309 --> 00:27:23,549
Let's go, Tibbs. It's time.

455
00:27:42,531 --> 00:27:45,971
Got a dead man walking here!

456
00:28:30,089 --> 00:28:32,911
Any last words, Tibbs?

457
00:28:38,608 --> 00:28:41,690
I'm sorry for you, sir.

458
00:28:42,379 --> 00:28:45,040
She was a nice girl.

459
00:28:45,040 --> 00:28:49,293
Maybe this will help you somehow.

460
00:28:59,470 --> 00:29:05,968
Last moment.
Time for truth, like you said.

461
00:29:05,968 --> 00:29:08,644
I'll tell it to you,

462
00:29:08,644 --> 00:29:13,200
but all it is is what 
I've been saying all along.

463
00:29:33,878 --> 00:29:35,891
Hello?

464
00:29:46,144 --> 00:29:49,171
Are you all right over there?

465
00:29:49,171 --> 00:29:51,067
Hello.

466
00:29:52,395 --> 00:29:54,638
Oh, god.

467
00:30:00,655 --> 00:30:02,662
I got to get help.

468
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:09,420
- Faith...
- What?

469
00:30:10,177 --> 00:30:14,831
- Faith.
- Faith?

470
00:30:14,831 --> 00:30:17,786
You found faith?

471
00:30:17,786 --> 00:30:21,118
Didn't I tell you you would?

472
00:30:21,118 --> 00:30:24,460
See, you're not alone, all right?

473
00:30:24,460 --> 00:30:27,005
I'm gonna go get help.

474
00:30:27,005 --> 00:30:29,507
Don't leave me.

475
00:30:38,979 --> 00:30:42,346
There's something out there
bigger than what's eating me alive.

476
00:30:42,346 --> 00:30:44,622
Something better.

477
00:30:44,622 --> 00:30:47,936
And if that little girl found it,

478
00:30:47,936 --> 00:30:50,776
I'll find it, too.

479
00:30:50,776 --> 00:30:53,898
I gotta believe that.

480
00:30:53,898 --> 00:30:58,174
That I'll find some peace.

481
00:31:01,398 --> 00:31:07,335
Look into my eyes.
It has been there all along.

482
00:31:07,335 --> 00:31:10,443
Truth.

483
00:31:45,065 --> 00:31:48,668
Prove me innocent.

484
00:32:11,063 --> 00:32:13,948
Will, what are you doing?

485
00:32:13,948 --> 00:32:16,075
You know we don't got
a warrant to be here.

486
00:32:16,075 --> 00:32:18,500
Andre's letter.

487
00:32:18,500 --> 00:32:21,880
- Son of a bitch.
- I didn't believe him.

488
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:24,364
You believed the cop.
You should have been able to.

489
00:32:24,364 --> 00:32:28,326
Good thing Norman ate his gun
or I'd be feeding it to him right now.

490
00:32:28,326 --> 00:32:30,457
What's it say?

491
00:32:30,457 --> 00:32:32,098
"Dear, Mr. Lange."

492
00:32:32,098 --> 00:32:34,732
"I've been sitting
in this bar two hours now,"

493
00:32:34,732 --> 00:32:38,431
"trying to make sense of the
world on a piece of paper."

494
00:32:38,431 --> 00:32:40,548
"But maybe there's just
this place in the end,"

495
00:32:40,548 --> 00:32:46,071
"this drink I'm staring into,
this last stop on the road."

496
00:32:54,157 --> 00:32:56,233
"Today I told your girl there's
something bigger out there,"

497
00:32:56,233 --> 00:32:59,860
"something better,
and she's got to find it."

498
00:33:09,293 --> 00:33:11,007
"Make sure she does."

499
00:33:11,007 --> 00:33:13,706
"'Cause it's out there,
it's got to be out there."

500
00:33:13,706 --> 00:33:16,001
"Don't lose her like I lost my family,"

501
00:33:16,001 --> 00:33:18,190
"like my boss fell out with his daughter."

502
00:33:18,190 --> 00:33:22,730
"just up and ran away,
no idea where she went."

503
00:33:27,244 --> 00:33:29,804
"She's got to keep looking. Me, too."

504
00:33:29,804 --> 00:33:32,914
"'Cause I know, one day,
we'll both find it."

505
00:33:32,914 --> 00:33:35,938
Signed, Andre Tibbs.

506
00:33:35,938 --> 00:33:39,429
So Andre's boss's daughter split on him?

507
00:33:39,429 --> 00:33:41,129
Got to be Wayne, right?

508
00:33:41,129 --> 00:33:45,759
Wayne, who goes around saying
how close he and his kid are?

509
00:33:45,759 --> 00:33:48,028
What the hell is this?

510
00:33:48,028 --> 00:33:51,074
You jerk me around for three days,
when you knew this was here?

511
00:33:51,074 --> 00:33:53,817
The Lange case is closed.

512
00:33:53,817 --> 00:33:58,256
You lie to my face, let a man die.

513
00:33:58,256 --> 00:34:00,252
And you're giving me a tone?

514
00:34:00,252 --> 00:34:02,714
There is nothing there. Nothing.

515
00:34:02,714 --> 00:34:05,269
You're no better than Norman.

516
00:34:05,556 --> 00:34:09,817
Kate's killer was executed last night.

517
00:34:09,817 --> 00:34:17,313
- Now, do I need to say it any slower?
- No.

518
00:34:17,313 --> 00:34:20,955
That's just right.

519
00:34:24,986 --> 00:34:26,593
You're done.

520
00:34:26,593 --> 00:34:28,798
You're gonna be back in blues!

521
00:34:28,798 --> 00:34:31,999
You're gonna be riding a mount for this!

522
00:34:34,752 --> 00:34:38,250
Wayne Nelson's daughter, 
the one he claims he's so close with?

523
00:34:38,250 --> 00:34:42,349
Turns out she booked out 12 years ago.
No contact since.

524
00:34:42,349 --> 00:34:43,948
Not my definition of "close."

525
00:34:43,948 --> 00:34:46,889
And guess what her name is? Faith.

526
00:34:46,889 --> 00:34:50,446
And "Faith" is what Kate was saying,
right when she died.

527
00:34:50,446 --> 00:34:52,119
Maybe a coincidence.

528
00:34:52,119 --> 00:34:56,276
- We track her down?
- Nah. Lil's talking to her now.

529
00:34:57,182 --> 00:34:59,865
I know this is hard to talk about, Faith.

530
00:34:59,865 --> 00:35:02,946
It was 12 years ago.
I'm okay.

531
00:35:03,464 --> 00:35:08,418
Your dad's under investigation
for a young girl's death.

532
00:35:08,944 --> 00:35:10,807
Okay.

533
00:35:12,464 --> 00:35:15,326
And that doesn't surprise you?

534
00:35:15,581 --> 00:35:17,776
Not really.

535
00:35:17,776 --> 00:35:22,087
I know there's not too many reasons
a girl would walk out on her dad

536
00:35:22,087 --> 00:35:25,258
and never look back.

537
00:35:25,712 --> 00:35:27,862
No.

538
00:35:28,505 --> 00:35:30,814
When did it start?

539
00:35:30,814 --> 00:35:33,315
When I was 13.

540
00:35:33,315 --> 00:35:36,097
I thought it was normal.

541
00:35:38,225 --> 00:35:39,791
How could you know different?

542
00:35:39,791 --> 00:35:44,073
By your learning.
Day after graduation, I was gone.

543
00:35:44,073 --> 00:35:51,178
Heard from my friends he was calling 
them 20 times a day, frantic to find me.

544
00:35:51,178 --> 00:35:53,505
- Did he?
- No.

545
00:35:53,505 --> 00:35:57,787
And then, one day,
he just stops calling.

546
00:35:57,787 --> 00:35:59,726
Never heard from him again.

547
00:35:59,726 --> 00:36:01,413
You remember when that was?

548
00:36:01,413 --> 00:36:03,625
Never forgot.

549
00:36:03,625 --> 00:36:06,930
June '94.

550
00:36:06,930 --> 00:36:10,468
That's the same month 
Kate Lange was killed.

551
00:36:17,850 --> 00:36:20,296
You know what your detective
did to me this morning?

552
00:36:20,296 --> 00:36:21,715
It's going around.

553
00:36:21,715 --> 00:36:23,899
I want to know how
he's gonna be disciplined.

554
00:36:23,899 --> 00:36:26,940
Danner, he watched a man
die last night.

555
00:36:26,940 --> 00:36:28,669
Heat broke.

556
00:36:28,669 --> 00:36:30,931
Andre was right.

557
00:36:33,269 --> 00:36:36,017
Got Wayne Nelson's phone records.

558
00:36:36,017 --> 00:36:38,652
There was one outgoing call made
the night of Kate's death.

559
00:36:38,652 --> 00:36:40,788
To the Lange house.

560
00:36:41,434 --> 00:36:44,057
Nelson's here now.

561
00:36:48,025 --> 00:36:50,475
Go do the interview.

562
00:36:53,874 --> 00:36:56,521
All I'm seeing here is business as usual.

563
00:36:56,521 --> 00:36:58,473
I said I want that detective punished.

564
00:36:58,473 --> 00:36:59,942
Yeah, I heard you.

565
00:36:59,942 --> 00:37:05,188
But this is our house,
and I said he's doing the interview.

566
00:37:06,981 --> 00:37:10,744
Don't make me drop-kick you out of here.

567
00:37:17,630 --> 00:37:21,019
So you said something about a follow-up?

568
00:37:21,433 --> 00:37:24,846
- New developments.
- Like?

569
00:37:24,846 --> 00:37:28,794
Like you talking on the phone with Kate 
Lange, the night she was murdered.

570
00:37:28,794 --> 00:37:31,986
- What?
- That's what I said.

571
00:37:31,986 --> 00:37:33,956
Saying you didn't hear
Andre's pager, Wayne?

572
00:37:33,956 --> 00:37:37,201
The one he left behind.
You didn't make a call?

573
00:37:37,201 --> 00:37:39,054
No, no, no, no.
You're right.

574
00:37:39,054 --> 00:37:42,105
- Uh, but she was looking for Andre.
- Good answer.

575
00:37:42,105 --> 00:37:45,049
'Cause we checked
with the phone company.

576
00:37:45,049 --> 00:37:48,189
Yeah, in fact, uh...

577
00:37:48,189 --> 00:37:52,469
It was funny because, um,
at first, she thought I was Andre.

578
00:37:52,469 --> 00:37:54,128
Recall how that went?

579
00:37:54,128 --> 00:37:56,991
Yeah, I called her back,
and she was off and running,

580
00:37:56,991 --> 00:37:58,745
saying she wanted to finish our talk.

581
00:37:58,745 --> 00:38:02,619
Of course, uh, I stopped her,
and set her straight that it was me.

582
00:38:02,619 --> 00:38:05,180
Sure you didn't
take advantage of the mix-up?

583
00:38:05,180 --> 00:38:10,927
For a guy like you, had to be
an opportunity of a lifetime.

584
00:38:10,927 --> 00:38:13,611
- A guy like me?
- We know about Faith,

585
00:38:13,611 --> 00:38:16,811
what you were doing to her
all those years.

586
00:38:16,811 --> 00:38:20,647
- I don't like what you're implying.
- I don't like it either, Wayne.

587
00:38:20,647 --> 00:38:23,019
In fact, it makes me sick.

588
00:38:23,019 --> 00:38:24,572
I know what you are.

589
00:38:24,572 --> 00:38:27,769
A degenerate like you gets a chance
to prey on a teenage girl,

590
00:38:27,769 --> 00:38:30,901
and it's only weeks after Faith
walked out forever.

591
00:38:30,901 --> 00:38:33,619
- Don't talk about Faith!
- I'll talk about her all I want.

592
00:38:33,619 --> 00:38:36,951
And, by the way, she hates your guts.

593
00:38:36,951 --> 00:38:39,850
So, now, along comes another young girl,

594
00:38:39,850 --> 00:38:42,048
one who reminds you of Faith.

595
00:38:42,048 --> 00:38:44,645
You hear her voice on
the other line, late at night...

596
00:38:44,645 --> 00:38:47,443
Don't tell me you're not going
over to get your jollies.

597
00:38:47,443 --> 00:38:49,550
You were missing your daughter.

598
00:38:49,550 --> 00:38:53,444
Maybe you only meant to 
go talk with this girl.

599
00:38:57,967 --> 00:39:00,736
She wasn't half as sweet as my Faith.

600
00:39:00,736 --> 00:39:03,581
'Cause she wasn't beaten down by you.

601
00:39:03,581 --> 00:39:05,600
Probably told you to keep
your dirty hands off her.

602
00:39:05,600 --> 00:39:08,875
Oh, you got a sharp mouth.

603
00:39:09,435 --> 00:39:11,900
She talked back to me...

604
00:39:11,900 --> 00:39:14,085
